Lord of the Rings - Citatsamling
1.
"Even the smallest person can change the course of the future."
"Not all those who wander are lost."
"There is some good in this world, and it's worth fighting for."
"All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given us."
"I would rather share one lifetime with you than face all the ages of this world alone."
"A day may come when the courage of men fails... but it is not this day."
"It is not the strength of the body, but the strength of the spirit."
"The world is indeed full of peril, and in it there are many dark places."
"There's some good in this world, Mr. Frodo, and it's worth fighting for."
"One does not simply walk into Mordor."
"I'm glad to be with you, Samwise Gamgee, here at the end of all things."
"So do all who live to see such times.
But that is not for them to decide."
"It is a strange fate that we should suffer so much fear and doubt over so small a thing."
"There is no curse in Elvish, Entish, or the tongues of Men for this treachery."
"The horn of Gondor shall not have been blown in vain!"
It was made by those who are Dead, and the Dead keep it."
"That still only counts as one!"
"They're taking the Hobbits to Isengard!"
"This day does not belong to one man but to all.

Let us together rebuild this world that we may
share in the days of peace."
"Deeds will not be less valiant because they are unpraised."
"There's only one Lord of the Ring, only one who can bend it to his will.
"Even in the darkest moments, hope can still shine through."
"We swears to serve the master of the Precious.
We will swear on... on the Precious!"
"I will not say: do not weep; for not all tears are an evil."
"The closer we are to danger, the farther we are from harm."
"I will take the Ring, though I do not know the way."
"This task was appointed to you.
And if you do not find a way, no one will."
"You are the luckiest, the canniest, and the most reckless man I ever knew."
"I can't carry it for you, but I can carry you!"
"You must understand, young hobbit, it takes a long time to say anything in Old Entish.

And we
never say anything unless it is worth taking a long time to say."
"I thought up an ending for my book: And he lives happily ever after, till the end of his days."
"That's not for them to decide.
All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given us."
"A hunted man sometimes wearies of distrust and longs for friendship."
"I think we should get off the road."
"A wizard is never late, nor is he early.
He arrives precisely when he means to."
"My friends... you bow to no one."
"If by my life or death I can protect you, I will."
He is the lord of all horses, and has been my friend through many dangers."

"And thus it was that a Fourth Age of Middle-earth began, and the Fellowship of the Ring...
though eternally bound by friendship and love... was ended."
Everywhere I went, he was there."
"You must understand, the Ring is trying to get back to its master.
"It is but a shadow and a thought that you love.
I cannot give you what you seek."
"You are bound to me now, through your allegiance to Gondor."
"If you want him, come and claim him!"
"No parent should have to bury their child."
Ride for ruin and the world's ending!"
"A red sun rises, blood has been spilled this night."
"The power of Isengard is at your command, Sauron, Lord of the Earth."
"Against the power of Mordor there can be no victory."
"I would have followed you, my brother... my captain... my king."
"There is evil there that does not sleep."
"There are some things that time cannot mend.

Some hurts that go too deep... that have taken
hold."

Every path you have trod through wilderness, through war, has led to this
road."
"I go to my fathers, in whose mighty company I shall not now feel ashamed."
"You shall dwell in the house of your father, and the peace of your people shall be yours."
"There will come a day when I no longer have strength to fight... but it is not this day!"
"White shores... and beyond, a far green country under a swift sunrise."
"And I suppose you think that was terribly clever."
"I will be dead before I see the Ring in the hands of an Elf!"
"We shall have peace, when you answer for the burning of the Westfold!"
"Leave all that can be spared behind.
